                    <BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />keplers wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Having established that The Shadow Being is not elsewhere and that this is not an illusion, Cenisa motions for the others to stop - as the team's diplomat, it is her job to deal with these situations.&nbsp; "So," she says calmly and politely, "you have some business here?"&nbsp;</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P><EM><FONT color="#000000">"Not exactly. I came here looking for something of mine, as I thought it would most logically be here. I had no idea there was a Brotherhood fortress set up. However, I have since learned the location of the thing I'm looking for from some Exo-Toa, and, as of now, am currently trying to come up with a plan to retrieve it."</FONT></EM></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>"Would something similar to an Exo-Toa do?" Cenisa asks.&nbsp; "I think that we could provide you with some fighting machines on our own - provided you can prove to us that you will not use them for tasks that we would consider morally reprehensible."</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P><EM><FONT color="#000000">"...That wouldn't help at all. In fact, if you did give it to me, I would think I might be tempted to use them for tasks you would consider morally wrong; despite the fact that I myself would find the actions wrong as well, this particular object is difficult to recapture..."</FONT></EM></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>"And the object in question?"</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P><FONT color="#000000">*With a sigh, The Shadow Being proceeds to use Illusion to produce what appears to be...a 3D model of an orange blob with eyes.*</FONT></P><P><EM><FONT color="#000000">"Experiment #6682. Meant to be the ultimate combat aid. It worked. 6682 is a creature that only seeks to help those whose morals are that of the Three Virtues, and, as a result, that's why I went here. However, once it's on a 'host'...it's nearly impossible to remove by force without smashing said Toa or whatever being it's on. Problem is, I don't want to smash anyone. See the problem?"</FONT></EM></P>
                
            
			
