                    <BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />keplers wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />BIONICHARGE wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />goldeaglefire wrote:<BR /><P><EM><FONT color="#000000">"...That wouldn't help at all. In fact, if you did give it to me, I would think I might be tempted to use them for tasks you would consider morally wrong; despite the fact that I myself would find the actions wrong as well, this particular object is difficult to recapture..."</FONT></EM></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>"And the object in question?"</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P><FONT color="#000000">*With a sigh, The Shadow Being proceeds to use Illusion to produce what appears to be...a 3D model of an orange blob with eyes.*</FONT></P><P><EM><FONT color="#000000">"Experiment #6682. Meant to be the ultimate combat aid. It worked. 6682 is a creature that only seeks to help those whose morals are that of the Three Virtues, and, as a result, that's why I went here. However, once it's on a 'host'...it's nearly impossible to remove by force without smashing said Toa or whatever being it's on. Problem is, I don't want to smash anyone. See the problem?"</FONT></EM></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>"Could you not simply turn the being intangible for long enough to remove the creature?&nbsp; And, if I may ask, what would such a creature do?"</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P><EM>"While I'm intangible naturally, while nothing can touch me, I can't touch anything. The telekinesis I used on you isn't an option either; it has insane strength, and removing it would also require removing the body part it was on. As for what it does...it can copy the limbs of any person it has contacted, can copy the powers of whoever it is currently on flawlessly, and doesn't drain said 'hosts' energy reserves."</EM></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Why I have allowed this to go on in my borders is beyond me. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>They are caught by a guard post that immediately lets Cordak&nbsp;at them.</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>OOC: What precisely do you mean by a 'guard post'?</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>OOC: Like a guard station posted on the perimeter of a fortification. Also, forgive my messup, I meant Cordak.</P>
                
            
			
